  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Exit Grant-Sustaining Empowered Communities of Resilience</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Resilience and sustainability of economic enterprises and support services to community groups and partner institutions are firmed up, strengthened and scaled up through improved facilities, business services, organizational governance, marketing and management competencies.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Throughout the partnership between I-CODE and CAid, I-CODE has facilitated relations and partnering between community livelihood groups, local government agencies and private businesses. This exit grant will be used to transition the livelihoods and enterprises of community groups towards market viability.  The key activities therefore are: 
&gt; planning sessions with stakeholders
&gt; profiling and evaluation of community livelihood and enterprise groups - seaweed enterprise, coastal resource management and mangroves rehabilitation project, food processing group, solar enterprise and electronic services
&gt; provision/leveraging seed funding
&gt; linking and partnership building between community livelihood/enterprise groups with business sector
&gt; continue promoting Community Managed Savings and Credit Association or CoMSCA to create a system of local pool of capital to provide members access to useful lump sums</narrative>
  </description>
